cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it presents a black-box attack against API call-based machine learning malware classifiers. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves generating adversarial examples and evaluating the effectiveness of the attack against various machine learning architectures. Additionally, it may be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it pertains to the security of software systems. Finally, it could also be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as adversarial attacks are a common topic in the field of computer vision.
